  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So-- and-- and then-- I'm sure you know Shakespeare play, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] what's it? that was his-- that was his position, and that was his downfall, because he-- he-- the Catholics don't-- I mean, they don't-- are not allowed to take, usually-- you probably know that, too-- if they-- if they lent them money.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So this was left to the Jews, and then when like Shylock came back for his money, so that was his downfall.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So were you experiencing--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, in-- in a funny way-- I was going-- I was going to a Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't know any non-Jewish people, except for the-- some stories.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You make-- and even then.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think in the apartment house where we lived, there was maybe one or two non-Jewish families, and the concierge.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So you knew about anti-Semitism, but until a certain point, you really did not-- you really didn't really personally feel it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I mean, I mean, the papers were full, and the Jewish press was full-- there were a lot of Jewish newspapers-- it was about-- there was constantly something going on in the parliament, you know, about the kosher slaughter that shouldn't be allowed, about, for instance, the stores were-- it was very, very strict, forbidden to sell anything on a Sunday.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So if you went-- if you ran out of-- of milk-- you never did, because there was always somebody to bring the milk to the house-- but I mean, life was so primitive.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But if you ran out of something and you went to the grocery store from, you know, from the back door, if a policeman caught you or caught the grocer who sell-- sold it to you, you were paying a high fine.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
